    "last_edit_date" : 1375866856,
    "creation_date" : 1375866522,
    "answer_id" : 18099206,
    "question_id" : 18099127,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Actually you don't need to write it. You have it by default. Sometimes you can create <code>private</code> constructor to prevent users to use default</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class MyClass{\n\nprivate MyClass(){} \n\n} \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For singelton patterns, for example you can block using default constructor.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Sometimes, when you use <code>Gson</code> plugin to convert String Json data to Object, it demands to write default constructor, otherwise it doesn't work</strong></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2032619,
      "reputation" : 2047,
      "user_id" : 1815873,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 50,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f832472ed5fd8c8c8b1425b068588af4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "JavaNewbie_M107",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1815873/javanewbie-m107"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1375866635,
    "creation_date" : 1375866635,
    "answer_id" : 18099244,
    "question_id" : 18099127,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>From the JPA tag, I suppose that you are working with Java beans. Every bean needs to have the following properties:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Getters and setters for all its main instance variables.</p></li>\n<li><p>An <strong>empty constructor.</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>All its instance variables should preferably be <code>private</code>.</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Thus the statement : \"every entity needs an empty constructor\".</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2648978,
      "reputation" : 918,
      "user_id" : 2291134,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d891ab2a8075283e04c4d535fc6fc0e1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "gjman2",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2291134/gjman2"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1375866780,
    "creation_date" : 1375866780,
    "answer_id" : 18099305,
    "question_id" : 18099127,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java not always give you a default invisible empty constructor if your class got argument constructor, you have to define the empty constructor by your own.</p>\n"
  }, {
