      "comment_id" : 98758743,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "no, you&#39;d only define one primary constructor for the persistence framework. You may have additional constructors though but the persistence framework needs to know which of the available constructors should be used to initialize the entity and that&#39;s what the @PersistenceConstructor annotation is for."
